  "title": "Azure Defender for SQL - Threat Protection",
  "contentHtml": "In this episode Michael, Gladys and Mark talk with guest Michael Makhlevich \n                  (\n                     <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://www.linkedin.com/in/michael-makhlevich-76794b121/'><i class=\"fa-brands fa-linkedin\"></i></a>\n                  ) \n                  \n                  about Azure Defender for SQL - Threat Protection. This is the first part of a two-part conversation about Azure Defender for SQL, next week will talk about Azure Defender for SQL - Vulnerability Analysis.\n                  &nbsp;In this episode, both Michael's discuss some history about SQL-related vulnerabilities and attacks. MichaelM also waxes\n                  philosophical about defending SQL databases, and it's not just about protecting data from attack!\n\n                  <br><br>\n                  We also discuss security news about Managed Hardware Security Module (HSM), App Config and Key Vault, Sentinel, Machine Learning, Azure Security Center and more.\n\n                  <br><br>\n                  <iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://player.rss.com/azsecpodcast/261425?theme=light\" class=\"podcast-player\" title=\"rss embed thingy\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><a href=\"https://rss.com/podcasts/azsecpodcast/261425/\">A Deep Look at Azure Defender for SQL - Threat Protection | RSS.com Podcasting</a></iframe>\n\n                  <h5>Links</h5> \n                  <ul>\n                     <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://rss.com/podcasts/azsecpodcast/261425/'>Transcript <i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i></a></li>\n                     <li><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\" href='https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/samples/azure/azure-sdk-for-net/app-secrets-configuration/?tabs=visualstudio'>Configure Applications with App Configuration and Key Vault</a></li>\n            